g bank fraud.","summary":"Supreme Court backs Bank of India in ₹1,500 crore loan default case.\nCourt clarifies guidelines on classifying bank fraud.","url":"https://sqst.in/shareMessage?msgId=814124979824509266","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-24T18:52:00","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"811533452452424448","title":"Bank of India to exercise call option on 9.3% Additional Tier I Bonds Series VII.\nRecord date set for 13th March 2026; bonds issued in March 2021 with a 5-year tenor.","summary":"Bank of India to exercise call option on 9.3% Additional Tier I Bonds Series VII.\nRecord date set for 13th March 2026; bonds issued in March 2021 with a 5-year tenor.","url":"https://sqst.in/LEJqh","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-17T15:14:12","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"260215154330483","title":"RBI's revised guidelines on acquisition financing enable Indian banks like SBI, Bank of India, and Kotak Mahindra Bank to participate in M&A, refinancing, and stake hikes with eased equity requirements.\nThe new norms allow unlisted firms with Rs 500 crore net worth and 3-year profitability to access financing, boosting domestic consolidation and capex in sectors like manufacturing and healthcare.","summary":"RBI's revised guidelines on acquisition financing enable Indian banks like SBI, Bank of India, and Kotak Mahindra Bank to participate in M&A, refinancing, and stake hikes with eased equity requirements.\nThe new norms allow unlisted firms with Rs 500 crore net worth and 3-year profitability to access financing, boosting domestic consolidation and capex in sectors like manufacturing and healthcare.","url":"https://www.financialexpress.com/business/banking-finance/banks-to-drive-domestic-mampa-as-rbi-eases-financing-norms/4143843/","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-15T19:07:00","source":"Financial Express"},{"id":"260212152443272","title":"ED attaches ₹1.03-cr assets of suspended BOI officer Hitesh Singla in ₹16.8-cr scam.\nSingla allegedly siphoned ₹16.8 cr from 230 customer accounts over two years under PMLA.","summary":"ED attaches ₹1.03-cr assets of suspended BOI officer Hitesh Singla in ₹16.8-cr scam.\nSingla allegedly siphoned ₹16.8 cr from 230 customer accounts over two years under PMLA.","url":"https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/mumbai-news/ed-attaches-1-03-cr-assets-of-suspended-boi-officer-in-16-8-cr-scam-101770835986133-amp.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-12T06:16:11","source":"Hindustan Times"},{"id":"807243932845716608","title":"India Ratings reaffirmed Bank of India's Tier II and infra bond ratings at IND AA/Stable.\nIssuer rating and AT1 bonds withdrawn; reflects systemic importance, better capital, and govt support.","summary":"India Ratings reaffirmed Bank of India's Tier II and infra bond ratings at IND AA/Stable.\nIssuer rating and AT1 bonds withdrawn; reflects systemic importance, better capital, and govt support.","url":"https://sqst.in/shareMessage?msgId=807243932845716590","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-05T19:09:11","source":"ScoutQuest"},{"id":"464212","title":"Nifty fell 2.96% to 24,571.75, Sensex dropped 2.88% to 79,899.42 due to STT hike, modest capex, and no major defense announcements.\nPSU banks like Bank of India and BoB declined; metals saw volatility, with silver down 9% and gold futures down 3%.","summary":"Nifty fell 2.96% to 24,571.75, Sensex dropped 2.88% to 79,899.42 due to STT hike, modest capex, and no major defense announcements.\nPSU banks like Bank of India and BoB declined; metals saw volatility, with silver down 9% and gold futures down 3%.","url":"https://www.ndtvprofit.com/markets/nifty-sensex-crash-on-budget-day-stt-hike-to-modest-capex-heres-eight-reasons-why-10923972#publisher=newsstand","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-01T13:07:34","source":"NDTV Profit"},{"id":"464173","title":"PSU Bank stocks fell sharply after Budget 2026 due to record borrowing of ₹17.2 lakh crore by the government.\nBank of India, Indian Bank, Bank of Maharashtra, and Bank of Baroda lost 5-6% ami